# The ruled drop model at file scope (issue #49): a top-level owning binding,
# a move out of it, and a block whose alloc frees at its own exit. The file
# driver drains the top level's teardowns at program exit, so this runs clean
# and prints its tail value with no leak or double free.
a := alloc i32 40
b := own a
inner := ( c := alloc i32 100  c@ )
b@ + inner - 98
